Stable Diffusion creators launch Black Forest Labs, secure $31M for ...
  URL: https://venturebeat.com/ai/stable-diffusion-creators-launch-black-forest-labs-secure-31m-for-flux-1-ai-image-generator
  Stable Diffusion creators launch Black Forest Labs, secure $31M for FLUX.1 AI image generator. Michael Nuñez. 1:52 pm, PT, August 1, 2024.

  --- Content ---
  [Michael Nuñez](https://venturebeat.com/author/michael_nunez)
  
  1:52 pm, PT, August 1, 2024
  
  
  ![Screenshot](https://venturebeat.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fimages.ctfassets.net%2Fjdtwqhzvc2n1%2F20EeJA3F9YGZhft9i4y6OT%2F3945055832d5db8d8c9c821721041bcd%2FScreenshot-2024-08-01-at-1.19.47_PM.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26q%3D100&w=3840&q=85)
  
  [Add to Google Preferred Source](https://www.google.com/preferences/source?q=venturebeat.com "Add to Google Preferred Source")
  
  [Black Forest Labs](https://blackforestlabs.ai/), a startup founded by the original creators of Stable Diffusion, unveiled its brand new [FLUX.1](https://blackforestlabs.ai/#get-flux) text-to-image model suite today, injecting new life into the open-source artificial intelligence community.
  
  This launch marks a potential watershed moment for accessible and powerful generative AI technology.
  
  Twitter Embed
  
  The company, led by Robin Rombach, Patrick Esser, and Andreas Blattmann, has [secured $31 million](https://blackforestlabs.ai/announcing-black-forest-labs/) in seed funding. [Andreessen Horowitz](https://a16z.com/announcement/investing-in-black-forest-labs/) (a16z) spearheaded the investment round, with additional backing from notable figures including [Brendan Iribe](https://www.linkedin.com/in/brendaniribe/), [Michael Ovitz](https://www.michaelovitz.com/), and [Garry Tan](https://www.ycombinator.com/people/garry-tan).
  
  Black Forest Labs aims to develop cutting-edge generative deep learning models for images and videos while prioritizing widespread accessibility and transparency.
  
  ## FLUX.1: A trio of AI powerhouses challenging closed-source giants
  
  FLUX.1 comes in three variants: the closed-source [FLUX.1 \[pro\]](https://fal.ai/models/fal-ai/flux-pro) available via API, the open-weight [FLUX.1 \[dev\]](https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-dev) for non-commercial use, and [FLUX.1 \[schnell\]](https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-schnell), a faster version released under an Apache 2.0 license for personal and local development.
  
  All models boast an impressive 12 billion parameters and utilize a hybrid architecture of multimodal and parallel diffusion transformer blocks.
  
  Industry experts have quickly recognized FLUX.1's potential impact. [Bindu Reddy](https://twitter.com/bindureddy), a prominent AI community figure, hailed the release in a post on X.com.
  
  Twitter Embed
  
  "This is truly amazing news for multimodal AI! The march towards open-source AGI continues," she tweeted.
  
  Early demonstrations suggest FLUX.1's output quality rivals or even surpasses that of popular closed-source models like [Midjourney v6.0](https://www.midjourney-v6.com/) and [DALL-E 3](https://openai.com/index/dall-e-3/).
  
  The timing of FLUX.1's release proves crucial for open-source AI. Recent [turbulence](https://www.wsj.com/tech/ai/tech-investor-sean-parker-leads-rescue-of-struggling-ai-startup-0d2e2b3b) at Stability AI, the company behind Stable Diffusion, had raised concerns about the future of accessible, high-quality image generation models.
  
  Black Forest Labs' entry into this space could reinvigorate the open-source AI ecosystem and potentially accelerate innovation across various fields, from graphic design to scientific visualization.
  
  ## Ethical AI: Navigating the responsible development of generative models
  
  However, the launch also brings to the forefront important questions about [responsible AI development](https://www.americanprogress.org/article/generative-ai-should-be-developed-and-deployed-responsibly-at-every-level-for-everyone/) and deployment.
  
  Black Forest Labs has outlined strict usage guidelines, prohibiting the use of their technology for generating false information, non-consensual imagery, or any content that could harm individuals or groups.
  
  The company's commitment to transparency and ethical AI development will likely face close scrutiny as FLUX.1 gains traction.
  
  FLUX.1 introduces several technical innovations. The models employ " [flow matching](https://arxiv.org/abs/2210.02747)," a method that generalizes diffusion models, and incorporate rotary positional embeddings and parallel attention layers for enhanced performance and hardware efficiency.
  
  This approach has yielded impressive results in visual quality, prompt adherence, and output diversity.
  
  The impact of FLUX.1 could extend far beyond the AI research community. Graphic designers, digital artists, and creative professionals may discover new possibilities in the model's ability to generate high-quality images across a wide range of styles and aspect ratios.
  
  Additionally, the open nature of FLUX.1 [\[dev\]](https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-dev) and [\[schnell\]](https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-schnell) variants could spark a new wave of applications and integrations across various industries.
  
  ## From pixels to video: Black Forest Labs' vision for the future of AI-generated media
  
  Black Forest Labs has already set its sights on its next frontier: [state-of-the-art text-to-video systems](https://blackforestlabs.ai/up-next/). Success in this arena could further cement the company's position as a leader in generative media technology.
  
  As the AI landscape rapidly evolves, the launch of Black Forest Labs and FLUX.1 represents a significant milestone in the democratization of powerful AI tools. The company's entry will likely reshape competitive dynamics in the AI industry and influence the ongoing debate about [open-source versus closed-source](https://venturebeat.com/ai/open-source-ai-narrows-gap-with-tech-giants-new-benchmark-reveals/) development models.
  
  With its robust technical foundation, substantial funding, and commitment to accessibility, Black Forest Labs is poised to play a pivotal role in shaping the future of generative AI. As FLUX.1 and its successors mature and find their way into more applications, their impact will likely reverberate across numerous sectors, potentially transforming how we create and interact with visual media.
  
