  The AI image generation market grapples with models that falter on complex prompts, produce inconsistent anatomy or text, and lock users into proprietary systems, limiting customisation for creators and enterprises.
  
  Black Forest Labs solves this through FLUX, which grasps intent to craft visuals beyond camera limits, from hyper-realistic scenes to imaginative art, powering millions via top-ranked open models on Hugging Face and enterprise tools on fal.ai, Replicate, and TogetherAI.
  
  Today, the company announced a $300M Series B at a $3.25B valuation, co-led by AMP and [Salesforce Ventures](https://techfundingnews.com/openai-rival-anthropic-backer-salesforce-ventures-doubles-ai-fund-with-additional-500m/), with participation from [Andreessen Horowitz](https://techfundingnews.com/ai-startup-hebbia-snaps-130m-funding-led-by-andreessen-horowitz/), [NVIDIA](https://techfundingnews.com/nvidia-backed-vast-data-inks-1-17b-cloud-storage-deal-with-coreweave/), [Northzone](https://techfundingnews.com/oslos-riff-grabs-e14m-from-northzone-to-scale-enterprise-vibe-coding-platform/), [Creandum](https://techfundingnews.com/german-startup-plancraft-secures-e12m-from-creandum-to-digitalise-labour-industry/), [Earlybird VC](https://techfundingnews.com/neuracore-3m-preseed-robotics-infrastructure/), [General Catalyst](https://techfundingnews.com/emidat-snaps-e4m-from-general-catalyst-to-simplify-construction-emission-management/), and [BroadLight Capital](https://techfundingnews.com/british-ai-voice-cloning-startup-raises-180m-at-3-3b-valuation-for-bringing-dead-celebs-back-to-life-and-more/), bringing total funding to over $450M to scale visual intelligence.​
  
  ## Advancing generative media with transparency and responsibility
  
  Founded in 2024 by Robin Rombach, [Andreas Blattmann](https://www.linkedin.com/in/andreas-blattmann-479038186?miniProfileUrn=urn%3Ali%3Afs_miniProfile%3AACoAACvJi50Bp0iEZ8fkITlBt5Xn3JqKQ2f_rd4&lipi=urn%3Ali%3Apage%3Ad_flagship3_search_srp_all%3BMtFKRgo3TViCc4rKUXZlLw%3D%3D), Patrick Esser, and Dominik Lorenz, Black Forest Labs aims to reclaim independence, building open frontier systems that make imagination tangible for artists and enterprises alike. Co-founders developed latent diffusion models at Heidelberg and LMU Munich, contributing to Stability AI’s Stable Diffusion amid GPU shortages that exposed Big Tech’s dominance.
  
  FLUX employs rectified flow transformers and a 12B-parameter hybrid architecture for superior prompt adherence, anatomy, text rendering, and 4MP photorealism, with variants like Pro for low-latency production, Dev for open dev, and Schnell for speed.
  
  The platform also features multi-reference control up to 10 images, cost-efficiency, and minimal safeguards that enable unfiltered creativity, integrated via APIs and diffusers for seamless workflows.
  
  Unlike Midjourney’s closed Discord ecosystem, OpenAI’s censorship of DALL-E 3, Stability AI’s inconsistent updates, or Ideogram’s text weaknesses, FLUX leads benchmarks while partnering with Adobe, Canva, Meta, and Microsoft.
  
  ## What’s next?
  
  This funding accelerates R&D on FLUX.2 enhancements, text-to-video models for motion and storytelling, and infrastructure for enterprise-scale deployments amid booming demand.
  
  Black Forest Labs aims to expand hiring, fine-tune for brands, and open-source releases, solidifying itself as the go-to for visual AI in creative pipelines from Instagram filters to industrial design.
  
